main event: Two unidentified objects were detected by radar in the Chicago area on August 6, 1965, and were observed for 45 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were tracked for 45 minutes before losing radar contact., The observation was reported by two distant radar stations., Analysis indicated the objects may have been confused with balloons., The flight path of the objects was characterized by slow movement and appeared sporadically on radar., No physical evidence was found to support the sighting.
witness description: Radar stations in the Chicago area
